### Deploy Jaeger

https://github.com/uber/jaeger[jaeger] provides all the required resources to start the required http://uber.github.io/jaeger/[Jaeger] components to trace your microservices.

Jaeger is a distributed tracing system. It helps gather timing data needed to troubleshoot latency problems in microservice architectures.

image::images/jaeger.png[]

#### Deploy using oc CLI

Execute:

----
$ oc process -f ansible/jaeger-all-in-one-openshift-template.yml | oc create -f
$ oc expose service jaeger-all-in-one --name jaeger-msa-frontend --hostname=jaeger-helloworld-msa.<domain>" # link for MSA's frontend
$ oc env dc -l app JAEGER_SERVER_URL=jaeger-all-in-one  # redeploy all services with tracing
----

#### Enable the Jaeger Dashboard in the Frontend

Execute:
----
$ oc env dc/frontend JAEGER_SERVER_URL=true
----

#### Test the Jaeger console

Access: http://jaeger-helloworld-msa.rhel-cdk.10.1.2.2.xip.io/

